item.title: Canadian Science: Gr: 9- physics help
item.dc:creator: @_Zach ##Zach##
item.description:
@_Zach wrote:

I’m Canadian and I have kept all of my Gr. 11 Physcis notes. Too bad you need gr. 9 ones. Oh well. LOL

[quote=“BobDole81, post:4, topic:46766”]Yep, do a search on google and you’ll most definately come up with a ton of good results.

Here is one site I found which turned out to be a great resource: http://hyperphysics.phy-astr.gsu.edu/hbase/hframe.html
And of course the NIST physics site: http://physics.nist.gov/ (also has a nice list of SI units)[/quote]

^^^^^ That’s for grade 11 and 12, so it can’t really help the guy.
